						               													<description>Puffin Rock: Spin &amp;amp; Find game was developed to help children strengthen their memory and practice memory techniques. There are two ways of playing it - an easier and a more advanced mode.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has a spinner and tiles with characters. The characters are represented on the tiles multiple times in different environments and poses. The goal of the game is to find and get as many tiles as possible.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the basic game mode, children first mark the back of the tiles. They can draw their unique markings, shapes and doodles that will help them remember what is on the other side. The tiles are then placed face-down. In the second part of the game they spin the spinner and find the character that the arrow points to among the face-down tiles. The player with the most tiles at the end of the game wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the advanced game mode, extra tiles are added, with only some tiles marked, and additional rules apply that make the game even more challenging.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules include additional variants for a single player and cooperative gameplay.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
